-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Unilever, Deutsche Bank
-- 
-- Wed Jul 09, 2014 02:21AM EDT
-- None



July 9 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Unilever and Deutsche Bank, on Wednesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Unilever NV <UNc.AS>: Nomura cuts to reduce from neutral; target price to 29.70 euros  * Deutsche Bank <DBKGn.DE>: JP Morgan raises to overweight from neutralFollowing is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Wednesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. * Amadeus IT <AMA.MC>: Evercore starts with equal-weight rating; price target 31 euros * Beiersdorf <BEIG.DE>: Nomura raises target price to 84 euros from 83 euros; rating buy * Deutsche Bank <DBKGn.DE>: JP Morgan raises to overweight from neutral * Enagas <ENAG.MC>: Morgan Stanley raises target to 27 euros from 24 euros; overweight * Nestle <NESN.VX>: Nomura raises target price to Sfr 59 from Sfr 57; rating reduce * Oriflame <ORIsdb.ST>: Nomura cuts target price to Sek 150 from Sek 160; rating reduce * Thales <TCFP.PA>: JP Morgan raises to overweight from neutral * Thales <TCFP.PA>: JP Morgan raises price target to 54 euros from 52 euros * Unilever NV <UNc.AS>: Nomura cuts to reduce from neutral